    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-04T14:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-04T14:41:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/513</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-04T21:00:00+01:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1918, 9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3044. British Minister has given me, at my request, copy of reply from Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs to note mentioned in my 2424, April 29, 4 p.m.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d556fn1">Reply not printed; the note mentioned in the telegram of
                        Apr. 29 is the British Foreign Secretary’s memorandum of Apr. 25 to the
                        Netherland Minister in Great Britain, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1469">p. 1469</ref>.</note> British Legation has telegraphed
                    summary to London and translation in full is being forwarded to you in today’s
                    pouch, as well as to American Embassy, London.</p>
                <p>In addition to a lengthy argument, the note says that the Netherlands Government
                    is ready at once to resume negotiations at The Hague for the rationing of
                    Holland. The Minister for Foreign Affairs, in a personal note to me, writes: “I
                    sincerely hope your Government will agree to have the negotiations carried on
                    here, which will much facilitate matters for us in connection with credits,
                    etc.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
